es**\\n\\nI’m considering the idea of avoiding library package usage for tests. It seems that a compile-time helper in the same package could be a reliable choice, even though it might go against the guideline of keeping tests outside library packages. The thought is that the helper could act as an access shim. However, this raises concerns because it’s recommended not to place tests in the same package to access package-private or internal code. Overall, it's not an ideal situation.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oZIOGanqrpaod6hteMOugjUw|fc_077308ce5e9d8ace0169f5af79d9a481a0b68db75bc68fdf31", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/BulkBeanTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.beans.BulkBean;", "newText": "import java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.beans.BulkBean;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void initializesBulkBeanInIsolatedClassLoader() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void resolvesLegacyClassLiteralHelperUsedByBulkBeanInitialization() throws Exception {\n        Method classLiteralHelper = BulkBean.class.getDeclaredMethod(\"class$\", String.class);\n        classLiteralHelper.setAccessible(true);\n\n        Object resolvedClass = classLiteralHelper.invoke(null, BulkBean.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(resolvedClass).isSameAs(BulkBean.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void initializesBulkBeanInIsolatedClassLoader() throws Exception {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1152, "output": 1894, "cacheRead": 45568, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48614, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777708898628, "responseId": "resp_077308ce5e9d8ace0169f5af63331481a0880654bf03